[2] Brazil (Para)
Date: Thu 28 Feb 2008
Source: Agencia Brasil [in Portuguese trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.agenciabrasil.gov.br/noticias/2008/02/28/mat>


In the metropolitan region of Belem in the state of Para in 2007, 15
387 cases of dengue were registered, of which 56 were dengue
hemorrhagic fever (DHF), and with 16 deaths. This year [2008], some
4838 cases of the disease have been reported, 16 of them DHF. In
2008, 6 deaths by this disease now have been confirmed.

According to the coordinator of the State Program of Dengue, Isa
Cruz, the result has been positive. "The number of notifications
increased due to awareness of medical and health professionals. This
indicates not that there are more cases of dengue this year [2008],
but comparing 2007 with 2008, 2008 had a greater monitoring by
professionals," she explained. [A sad situation, not looking ahead to
hide the obvious; it may be worse than it may appear. - Mod.LJS]

According to notes released by the Secretariat of Public Health of
Para [state], the Metropolitan region of Belem has 32 percent of the
resident population of Para. In the past 3 years, the city recorded
40 percent of cases of the disease and 50 percent of the DHF deaths.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT <promed@promedmail.org.com>

[A map showing the Brazilian states can be accessed at:
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/brazil.jpg>.
