[10] Viet Nam
Date: Sat 1 Mar 2008
Source: Thanh Nien News.com [edited]
<http://www.thanhniennews.com/healthy/?catid=8&newsid=36253>


Nearly 4000 individuals were infected with dengue fever this year
[2008], representing a 10 percent increase compared to the same
period last year [2007], the Ministry of Health said.

The disease, caused by _Anopheles_ mosquitoes [incorrect, see below -
Mod.TY], recently rose to 450 cases a week in the country and is
spreading mostly in the central and southern provinces, of which Ho
Chi Minh City, Tien Giang and Ben Tre are hardest hit.

Half of the current victims are adults, an abnormal phenomenon for
the disease that in previous cases had mostly befallen children.

The agency also forecast that up to 100 000 individuals may be
afflicted with transmission in 2008.

[Byline: Nam Son]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Brent Barrett

[The statement that dengue is caused by _Anopheles_ mosquitoes is
incorrect. Dengue is caused by 4 viruses transmitted by _Aedes
aegypti_ and _Ae. albopictus_ mosquitoes.

A map of Viet Nam showing the provinces can be accessed at:
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/vietnam_pol01.jpg>.
- Mod.TY]
